The paper discusses the problem of organizing resources in a cloud environment, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The proposed model for automatic scaling of cloud resources involves clustering and pattern recognition, which are techniques commonly used in Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the flexibility and scalability of cloud resources, which are topics related to Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
